            },
            "answer_text": "Probably? The triple alliance still wanted Paraguay around as a buffer state, and no one wanted to own the humanitarian disaster it had become. National reconstruction is an incredibly costly exercise and there\u2019s no indication that owning Paraguay would pay for it. For comparison\u2019s sake, look at the arguments against South Korea reuniting with North Korea. Sure the South would control the whole peninsula as a result, but it would also need to own and provide for millions of refugees. The demographic catastrophe was such that there weren\u2019t even enough people to enslave. ",
