            "answer_text": "This is a good question. That might very well have been the fate of my homeland, but there was Argentina as the other co-belligerent and they were having none of that \u201cBrazilian annexation\u201d nonsense. Jokes aside, the most commonly accepted view is that Paraguay was spared its national existence because it served as a buffer state between Argentina and Brazil. Of course, this didn\u2019t prevent neither Brazil nor Argentina from having substantial territorial gains. But both countries stopped short of annexation because an independent Paraguay was the best option for their interests. ",
